    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Material property and contact stiffness sensitivity analysis for pedicle screw FEA",
    "description": "A one-at-a-time sensitivity analysis was conducted varying cortical bone modulus (±15%), cancellous bone modulus (±30%), and screw-bone interface friction coefficient (0.2–0.6). Construct stiffness QoI varied by ±8.2% across the full parameter space, while yield force varied by ±6.7%, confirming that model predictions remain within the 10% acceptance bound under realistic material uncertainty. Contact stiffness was identified as the dominant driver of stiffness QoI sensitivity."
  },
